Patch Set 5:

copy/paste from my comment on https://review.tizen.org/gerrit/#/c/8162/:

We can find in the porting guide that the Bluetooth stack need a "BT Firmware Loading Module", this is bluetooth-tool + bluetooth-firmware-bcm

https://wiki.tizen.org/wiki/Porting_Guide/Connectivity

In source files of bluetooth-frwk:

bt-core/bt_core.c:127:	ret = system("/usr/etc/bluetooth/bt-stack-up.sh &");
bt-core/bt_core.c:147:	 if (system("/usr/etc/bluetooth/bt-stack-down.sh &") < 0) {
bt-core/bt_core.c:159:	if (system("/usr/etc/bluetooth/bt-stack-down.sh &") < 0) { 
bt-core/bt_core.c:221:	if (system("/usr/etc/bluetooth/bt-reset-env.sh &") < 0) { 
bt-core/bt_core.c:130:	 ret = system("/usr/etc/bluetooth/bt-dev-end.sh &");

bt-stack-up.sh, bt-stack-down.sh and bt-reset-env.sh are present in bluetooth-tools package. 
bt-dev-end.sh is present in bluetooth-firware-bcm package. 
(bluetooth-tools scripts call bluetooth-firmware-bcm scripts)

Note that bluetooth-firmware-bcm is an implementation for broadcom chip.

Please find related bug https://bugs.tizen.org/jira/browse/TBD-4 (Request to publish bluetooth-tools package)
